    &lt;Title&gt;Endoscopy Unit&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Garden985&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;In these difficult times it might be understandable for staff to have their focus slightly blurred. However on my experience today this is definitely not the case. Having been referred to endoscopy following an anomaly with a CT scan I was extremely nervous. However the gentleman who carried out the procedure did absolutely everything to allay my nerves. He firstly spent time explaining exactly what he was was going to do and then talked me through everything as it happened. After the procedure he then spent time explaining his findings and how to manage my ongoing condition.  
A difficult time made much easier by a clinician who actually cared.  
Thank you to all the team&lt;/CommentText&gt;
